SIMPLE: triparted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triparted
<hw>Tri"part`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>parted</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Parted into three piece; having
three parts or pieces; -- said of the field or of a bearing; <as>as, a
cross <ex>triparted</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Divided nearly to the base into
three segments or lobes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tripartible</ent>⟦br⟧
